    {"question_text": "What is the output of this code implementing the Event Sourcing pattern?\n\nclass EventStore:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.events = []\n    \n    def append(self, event):\n        self.events.append(event)\n    \n    def replay(self, initial_state):\n        state = initial_state.copy()\n        for event in self.events:\n            state = event['handler'](state, event['data'])\n        return state\n\nstore = EventStore()\nstore.append({'handler': lambda s, d: {**s, 'count': s.get('count', 0) + d}, 'data': 5})\nstore.append({'handler': lambda s, d: {**s, 'count': s.get('count', 0) + d}, 'data': 3})\nresult = store.replay({})\nprint(result)", "option_a": "{'count': 5}", "option_b": "{'count': 8}", "option_c": "{'count': 3}", "option_d": "{}", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
