    {"question_text": "What is the output of this code using the Decorator pattern (GoF) with multiple decorators?\n\nclass DataSource:\n    def read(self): return 'raw data'\n    def write(self, data): pass\n\nclass CompressionDecorator:\n    def __init__(self, source):\n        self._source = source\n    def read(self):\n        data = self._source.read()\n        return f'decompress({data})'\n\nclass EncryptionDecorator:\n    def __init__(self, source):\n        self._source = source\n    def read(self):\n        data = self._source.read()\n        return f'decrypt({data})'\n\nsource = EncryptionDecorator(CompressionDecorator(DataSource()))\nprint(source.read())", "option_a": "decompress(decrypt(raw data))", "option_b": "decrypt(decompress(raw data))", "option_c": "raw data", "option_d": "decompress(raw data)", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
