    {"question_text": "What is the output of this implementation of the Pipe and Filter pattern?\n\nclass Filter:\n    def process(self, data): return data\n\nclass StripFilter(Filter):\n    def process(self, data): return data.strip()\n\nclass LowerFilter(Filter):\n    def process(self, data): return data.lower()\n\nclass ReplaceFilter(Filter):\n    def __init__(self, old, new):\n        self.old = old\n        self.new = new\n    def process(self, data): return data.replace(self.old, self.new)\n\nclass Pipeline:\n    def __init__(self, *filters):\n        self.filters = filters\n    def execute(self, data):\n        for f in self.filters:\n            data = f.process(data)\n        return data\n\np = Pipeline(StripFilter(), LowerFilter(), ReplaceFilter(' ', '_'))\nprint(p.execute('  Hello World  '))", "option_a": "hello world", "option_b": "hello_world", "option_c": "Hello_World", "option_d": "  hello_world  ", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
