    {"question_text": "What is the output of this Service Locator pattern?\n\nclass ServiceLocator:\n    _services = {}\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def register(cls, name, service):\n        cls._services[name] = service\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def get(cls, name):\n        if name not in cls._services:\n            raise KeyError(f'Service {name} not found')\n        return cls._services[name]\n\nclass CacheService:\n    def get(self, key): return f'cached_{key}'\n\nServiceLocator.register('cache', CacheService())\nservice = ServiceLocator.get('cache')\nprint(service.get('user_1'))", "option_a": "user_1", "option_b": "cached_user_1", "option_c": "CacheService", "option_d": "KeyError", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
