    {"question_text": "What is the output of this CQRS (Command Query Responsibility Segregation) pattern?\n\nclass CommandBus:\n    _handlers = {}\n    @classmethod\n    def register(cls, command_type, handler):\n        cls._handlers[command_type] = handler\n    @classmethod\n    def dispatch(cls, command):\n        handler = cls._handlers.get(type(command))\n        if handler:\n            return handler(command)\n\nclass CreateUser:\n    def __init__(self, name): self.name = name\n\nCommandBus.register(CreateUser, lambda cmd: f'created: {cmd.name}')\nresult = CommandBus.dispatch(CreateUser('Alice'))\nprint(result)", "option_a": "Alice", "option_b": "created: Alice", "option_c": "CreateUser", "option_d": "None", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
