    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of the Iterator pattern for a paginated API response?\n\nclass PaginatedResults:\n    def __init__(self, fetch_page):\n        self._fetch = fetch_page\n        self._page = 0\n        self._buffer = []\n        self._exhausted = False\n    \n    def __iter__(self): return self\n    \n    def __next__(self):\n        while not self._buffer:\n            if self._exhausted:\n                raise StopIteration\n            items = self._fetch(self._page)\n            if not items:\n                self._exhausted = True\n                raise StopIteration\n            self._buffer = items\n            self._page += 1\n        return self._buffer.pop(0)\n\nWhat pattern does this implement?", "option_a": "Factory", "option_b": "Iterator with lazy loading - it fetches pages on demand as items are consumed", "option_c": "Observer", "option_d": "Proxy", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
    {"question_text": "What is the output?\n\nclass Publisher:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._subscribers = {}\n    \n    def subscribe(self, topic, callback):\n        self._subscribers.setdefault(topic, []).append(callback)\n    \n    def unsubscribe(self, topic, callback):\n        if topic in self._subscribers:\n            self._subscribers[topic].remove(callback)\n    \n    def publish(self, topic, message):\n        return [cb(message) for cb in self._subscribers.get(topic, [])]\n\npub = Publisher()\nhandler = lambda m: m * 2\npub.subscribe('numbers', handler)\npub.subscribe('numbers', lambda m: m + 10)\nresult1 = pub.publish('numbers', 5)\npub.unsubscribe('numbers', handler)\nresult2 = pub.publish('numbers', 5)\nprint(len(result1), len(result2))", "option_a": "1 1", "option_b": "2 1", "option_c": "2 2", "option_d": "2 0", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
    {"question_text": "What principle does the following refactoring demonstrate?\n\n# Before\nclass OrderService:\n    def calculate_total(self, order):\n        # 100 lines of pricing logic\n        pass\n    def apply_discount(self, order):\n        # 50 lines of discount logic\n        pass\n\n# After\nclass OrderService:\n    def __init__(self, pricing_strategy, discount_strategy):\n        self._pricing = pricing_strategy\n        self._discount = discount_strategy\n    def calculate_total(self, order):\n        total = self._pricing.calculate(order)\n        return self._discount.apply(total, order)", "option_a": "DRY principle", "option_b": "Composition over Inheritance - complex behavior is achieved by composing simple objects", "option_c": "YAGNI principle", "option_d": "Law of Demeter", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
    {"question_text": "What is the output of this implementation of the Specification pattern combined with the Repository pattern?\n\nclass InMemoryRepository:\n    def __init__(self, items):\n        self.items = items\n    def find(self, spec):\n        return [item for item in self.items if spec(item)]\n\ndef age_over(n):\n    return lambda item: item['age'] > n\n\ndef has_skill(skill):\n    return lambda item: skill in item.get('skills', [])\n\ndef and_spec(*specs):\n    return lambda item: all(spec(item) for spec in specs)\n\nrepo = InMemoryRepository([\n    {'name': 'Alice', 'age': 30, 'skills': ['python', 'ml']},\n    {'name': 'Bob', 'age': 25, 'skills': ['python']},\n    {'name': 'Charlie', 'age': 35, 'skills': ['java']}\n])\n\nresult = repo.find(and_spec(age_over(28), has_skill('python')))\nprint(len(result), result[0]['name'])", "option_a": "2 Alice", "option_b": "1 Alice", "option_c": "1 Charlie", "option_d": "0 IndexError", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
