    {"question_text": "What is the output of this implementation of the Visitor pattern?\n\nclass Element:\n    def accept(self, visitor): pass\n\nclass TextElement(Element):\n    def __init__(self, text): self.text = text\n    def accept(self, visitor): return visitor.visit_text(self)\n\nclass ImageElement(Element):\n    def __init__(self, url): self.url = url\n    def accept(self, visitor): return visitor.visit_image(self)\n\nclass HTMLVisitor:\n    def visit_text(self, element): return f'<p>{element.text}</p>'\n    def visit_image(self, element): return f'<img src=\"{element.url}\"/>'\n\nclass MarkdownVisitor:\n    def visit_text(self, element): return element.text\n    def visit_image(self, element): return f'![img]({element.url})'\n\nelements = [TextElement('hello'), ImageElement('pic.png')]\nmd = MarkdownVisitor()\nresult = [e.accept(md) for e in elements]\nprint(result[1])", "option_a": "<img src=\"pic.png\"/>", "option_b": "pic.png", "option_c": "![img](pic.png)", "option_d": "ImageElement", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
