    {"question_text": "What is the output?\n\nclass EventEmitter:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._once_handlers = {}\n        self._handlers = {}\n    \n    def on(self, event, handler):\n        self._handlers.setdefault(event, []).append(handler)\n    \n    def once(self, event, handler):\n        self._once_handlers.setdefault(event, []).append(handler)\n    \n    def emit(self, event, *args):\n        results = []\n        for h in self._handlers.get(event, []):\n            results.append(h(*args))\n        for h in self._once_handlers.pop(event, []):\n            results.append(h(*args))\n        return results\n\nemitter = EventEmitter()\nemitter.on('ping', lambda: 'pong')\nemitter.once('ping', lambda: 'first_pong')\n\nr1 = emitter.emit('ping')\nr2 = emitter.emit('ping')\nprint(len(r1), len(r2))", "option_a": "1 1", "option_b": "2 2", "option_c": "2 1", "option_d": "1 0", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
