    {"question_text": "What is the output?\n\nclass TaskQueue:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self._queue = []\n        self._history = []\n    \n    def enqueue(self, task):\n        self._queue.append(task)\n    \n    def execute_next(self):\n        if self._queue:\n            task = self._queue.pop(0)\n            result = task()\n            self._history.append(result)\n            return result\n        return None\n    \n    def execute_all(self):\n        while self._queue:\n            self.execute_next()\n        return self._history\n\nq = TaskQueue()\nq.enqueue(lambda: 'task_1')\nq.enqueue(lambda: 'task_2')\nq.enqueue(lambda: 'task_3')\nq.execute_next()\nresult = q.execute_all()\nprint(len(result))", "option_a": "2", "option_b": "1", "option_c": "3", "option_d": "0", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
