    {"question_text": "What is the output?\n\nclass TypeRegistry:\n    _registry = {}\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def register(cls, type_id):\n        def decorator(klass):\n            cls._registry[type_id] = klass\n            return klass\n        return decorator\n    \n    @classmethod\n    def create(cls, type_id, *args, **kwargs):\n        klass = cls._registry.get(type_id)\n        if klass:\n            return klass(*args, **kwargs)\n        raise ValueError(f'Unknown type: {type_id}')\n\n@TypeRegistry.register('circle')\nclass Circle:\n    def __init__(self, r): self.r = r\n    def area(self): return 3.14 * self.r ** 2\n\n@TypeRegistry.register('square')\nclass Square:\n    def __init__(self, s): self.s = s\n    def area(self): return self.s ** 2\n\nshape = TypeRegistry.create('square', 5)\nprint(shape.area())", "option_a": "78.5", "option_b": "3.14", "option_c": "10", "option_d": "25", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "design_patterns"},
