    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement JWT token refresh in an API client?\n\nclass APIClient:\n    def __init__(self, base_url, refresh_token):\n        self.base_url = base_url\n        self.refresh_token = refresh_token\n        self.access_token = None\n    \n    def _refresh(self):\n        resp = requests.post(f'{self.base_url}/auth/refresh',\n            json={'refresh_token': self.refresh_token})\n        self.access_token = resp.json()['access_token']\n    \n    def request(self, method, path, **kwargs):\n        if not self.access_token:\n            self._refresh()\n        headers = {'Authorization': f'Bearer {self.access_token}'}\n        resp = requests.request(method, f'{self.base_url}{path}', headers=headers, **kwargs)\n        if resp.status_code == 401:\n            self._refresh()\n            headers = {'Authorization': f'Bearer {self.access_token}'}\n            resp = requests.request(method, f'{self.base_url}{path}', headers=headers, **kwargs)\n        return resp\n\nWhat pattern does the 401 handling implement?", "option_a": "Circuit breaker", "option_b": "Observer", "option_c": "Factory", "option_d": "Transparent token refresh - automatically retry with new token on authentication failure", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},

