    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of multipart file upload via API?\n\nimport requests\n\ndef upload_file(url, file_path, token):\n    with open(file_path, 'rb') as f:\n        files = {'file': (file_path.split('/')[-1], f, 'application/octet-stream')}\n        headers = {'Authorization': f'Bearer {token}'}\n        response = requests.post(url, files=files, headers=headers)\n    return response\n\nWhat Content-Type header does requests automatically set for multipart uploads?", "option_a": "application/json", "option_b": "application/octet-stream", "option_c": "multipart/form-data with automatically generated boundary", "option_d": "text/plain", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
