    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement retry with jitter to prevent thundering herd?\n\nimport random\n\ndef retry_with_jitter(base_delay, attempt):\n    # Full jitter\n    return random.uniform(0, base_delay * 2 ** attempt)\n\nWhy is jitter important in retry logic?", "option_a": "It makes retries faster", "option_b": "It reduces server load", "option_c": "It spreads out retry attempts from multiple clients, preventing all clients from retrying simultaneously", "option_d": "It ensures retries happen at fixed intervals", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},

