    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of API request signing with HMAC for webhook verification?\n\ndef verify_signature(payload_body, signature_header, secret):\n    import hmac\n    import hashlib\n    expected_signature = 'sha256=' + hmac.new(\n        secret.encode('utf-8'),\n        msg=payload_body,\n        digestmod=hashlib.sha256\n    ).hexdigest()\n    return hmac.compare_digest(expected_signature, signature_header)", "option_a": "This correctly computes HMAC-SHA256 and uses timing-safe comparison to verify the webhook payload", "option_b": "This is incorrect because it should use MD5", "option_c": "This is incorrect because it should use base64", "option_d": "This is incorrect because signatures should use RSA", "correct_answer": "A", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
