    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to handle API deprecation notices?", "option_a": "Ignore them", "option_b": "Switch immediately to the new version", "option_c": "Stop using the API entirely", "option_d": "Log deprecation warnings, plan migration timeline, test new version in staging before switching", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of request prioritization in an API client?", "option_a": "Random order", "option_b": "Alphabetical by URL", "option_c": "Smallest payload first", "option_d": "Use a priority queue where critical operations (auth refresh, health checks) execute before bulk data operations", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct approach for implementing API client connection health monitoring?", "option_a": "Never check connection health", "option_b": "Reconnect before every request", "option_c": "Only check on errors", "option_d": "Periodically ping the server, track response times and error rates, preemptively refresh connections showing degradation", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response streaming for large datasets?", "option_a": "Load everything into memory", "option_b": "Use offset pagination", "option_c": "Download to a file first", "option_d": "Use chunked transfer encoding (Transfer-Encoding: chunked) and process response incrementally using iter_content/iter_lines", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct HTTP status code for a resource that existed but has been permanently deleted?", "option_a": "404 Not Found", "option_b": "204 No Content", "option_c": "301 Moved Permanently", "option_d": "410 Gone", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API client observability?", "option_a": "Log only errors", "option_b": "Don't log anything", "option_c": "Log every response body", "option_d": "Emit structured metrics (latency, error rate, throughput) and traces for each API call to enable monitoring and alerting", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct approach for handling API schema evolution?", "option_a": "Reject any new fields", "option_b": "Accept only the exact schema", "option_c": "Parse using regex", "option_d": "Use tolerant readers (ignore unknown fields) and strict writers (only send known fields) for forward/backward compatibility", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API request deduplication using bloom filters?", "option_a": "Store all request hashes in a list", "option_b": "Use a database for every request", "option_c": "Never deduplicate", "option_d": "Use a probabilistic bloom filter for fast approximate membership testing, with a backup store for confirmed duplicates", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response transformation for different client versions?", "option_a": "Force all clients to upgrade", "option_b": "Return different formats randomly", "option_c": "Use content negotiation only", "option_d": "Apply response transformers based on client version header, adapting the response shape to what each client version expects", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of API request bulkheading?", "option_a": "Use a single connection for everything", "option_b": "Share resources across all API calls", "option_c": "Never limit concurrent requests", "option_d": "Isolate API calls to different services into separate connection pools/semaphores so one failing service doesn't exhaust resources for others", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response envelope unwrapping?", "option_a": "Return the raw HTTP response always", "option_b": "Parse only the status code", "option_c": "Return the headers only", "option_d": "Extract the actual data from the envelope structure (e.g., response.json()['data']) based on the API's wrapper format", "correct_answer": "D", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of API request correlation across microservices?", "option_a": "Don't track requests", "option_b": "Use IP addresses for correlation", "option_c": "Generate a unique trace ID at the API gateway and propagate it through all downstream service calls via headers", "option_d": "Use timestamps only", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API client retry for network failures?", "option_a": "Never retry network failures", "option_b": "Retry immediately without delay", "option_c": "Retry with exponential backoff for connection errors and timeouts, as they are typically transient failures", "option_d": "Retry only once", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API request throttling on the client side?", "option_a": "Send requests as fast as possible", "option_b": "Only send one request per minute", "option_c": "Track request count per time window and delay/queue requests when approaching the limit to stay within rate constraints", "option_d": "Block all requests after the first one", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response validation?", "option_a": "Trust all responses from the server", "option_b": "Only check status codes", "option_c": "Validate response schema, types, and required fields; reject malformed responses early rather than propagating bad data", "option_d": "Only check for null values", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API request signing with timestamps for replay protection?", "option_a": "Don't include timestamps", "option_b": "Use timestamps only for logging", "option_c": "Include timestamp in the signed message; server rejects requests with timestamps outside an acceptable window (e.g., 5 minutes)", "option_d": "Use random nonces only", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response caching invalidation?", "option_a": "Never invalidate cache", "option_b": "Clear all caches every hour", "option_c": "Invalidate specific cache entries when the corresponding resource is modified (POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE) or when TTL expires", "option_d": "Cache everything forever", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API endpoint health checking?", "option_a": "Never check health", "option_b": "Check health only on errors", "option_c": "Periodically call a lightweight health endpoint to verify the service is responsive before sending real traffic", "option_d": "Check health after every request", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement progressive API response loading?", "option_a": "Load all data at once", "option_b": "Use random page sizes", "option_c": "Start with essential data (small first page), then progressively load additional data as needed using pagination or lazy loading", "option_d": "Load data in reverse order", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API client certificate authentication?", "option_a": "Send certificates in the request body", "option_b": "Include certificates in query parameters", "option_c": "Configure the HTTP client with client certificates (cert and key files) for mutual TLS authentication", "option_d": "Use certificates only for responses", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API request queueing for offline support?", "option_a": "Discard requests when offline", "option_b": "Throw errors immediately", "option_c": "Queue failed requests locally and automatically retry them when connectivity is restored, maintaining order", "option_d": "Only support online mode", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API client error recovery with fallbacks?", "option_a": "Always throw errors to the user", "option_b": "Try the primary endpoint first; on failure, attempt a fallback (cached data, secondary service, or degraded response) before failing", "option_c": "Ignore all errors", "option_d": "Retry the same endpoint indefinitely", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct approach for implementing API request compression?", "option_a": "Only compress responses", "option_b": "Set Content-Encoding: gzip on the request and compress the request body to reduce upload bandwidth for large payloads", "option_c": "Compress URLs", "option_d": "Use shorter field names instead", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation of API response streaming with Server-Sent Events?", "option_a": "Poll every second", "option_b": "Establish a long-lived HTTP connection where the server sends events as text/event-stream; client processes each event as it arrives", "option_c": "Use WebSockets always", "option_d": "Download the complete response first", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API client load balancing?", "option_a": "Always use the first server", "option_b": "Distribute requests across multiple backend servers using round-robin, least-connections, or weighted algorithms", "option_c": "Use random servers", "option_d": "Only use one server until it fails", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API key scoping?", "option_a": "Give all keys full access", "option_b": "Use different API keys with specific permissions/scopes for different operations (read-only, write, admin) to follow least privilege", "option_c": "Rotate keys daily without scoping", "option_d": "Use a single shared key for everything", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response field filtering?", "option_a": "Always return all fields", "option_b": "Accept a 'fields' query parameter (e.g., ?fields=id,name,email) that specifies which fields to include in the response, reducing payload size", "option_c": "Let clients filter after receiving", "option_d": "Remove fields randomly", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API webhook subscriptions?", "option_a": "Hard-code webhook URLs", "option_b": "Allow clients to register webhook URLs via API, specifying event types to subscribe to, with ability to update/delete subscriptions", "option_c": "Send all events to all clients", "option_d": "Require manual configuration for each webhook", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API request signing for AWS services?", "option_a": "Use basic authentication", "option_b": "Compute Signature V4: create canonical request, derive signing key from date and credentials, sign with HMAC-SHA256", "option_c": "Put credentials in the URL", "option_d": "Use API keys only", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct approach for implementing API error responses with problem details?", "option_a": "Return plain text errors", "option_b": "Follow RFC 7807 Problem Details format with type, title, status, detail, and instance fields for machine-readable error responses", "option_c": "Return HTML error pages", "option_d": "Only return status codes", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct way to implement API response transformation pipelines?", "option_a": "Return raw data always", "option_b": "Chain response transformers (deserialization -> validation -> mapping -> enrichment) to convert API responses into domain objects", "option_c": "Transform at the database level", "option_d": "Let consumers handle all transformation", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "api_integration"},
